The station was evacuated and closed due to a fire alarm activation, according to Thameslink. They said via Twitter: "Due to a fire alarm activation at the station, Farringdon station has been evacuated and closed. "Trains can continue to run, but will not stop at Farringdon until further notice." The London Fire Brigade have arrived at the scene. Witness at the scene Paul Hayes reported that he had been "turfed off" the train along with "few hundred" others.